18:
The cedar paneling inside the temple was carved with ornamental gourds
 and flower blossoms. Everything was cedar;
 not a stone could be seen.

21:
He set up the pillars at the portico
 of the sanctuary: he set up the right pillar and named it Jachin;
 then he set up the left pillar and named it Boaz.

48:
Solomon also made all the equipment in the 
Lord
’s temple: the gold altar; the gold table that the Bread of the Presence was placed on;

50:
the pure gold ceremonial bowls, wick trimmers, sprinkling basins, ladles,
 and firepans;
 and the gold hinges for the doors of the inner temple (that is, the most holy place) and for the doors of the temple sanctuary.

13:
I have indeed built an exalted temple
 for you,
a place for your dwelling forever.

19:
Yet you are not the one to build it;
instead, your son, your own offspring,
will build it for my name.”

51:
For they are your people and your inheritance;
you brought them out of Egypt,
out of the middle of an iron furnace.

24:
Pharaoh’s daughter moved from the city of David
 to the house that Solomon had built for her;
 he then built the terraces.

23:
They also built for themselves high places,
 sacred pillars,
 and Asherah poles on every high hill and under every green tree;

26:
So they took the bull that he gave them, prepared it, and called on the name of Baal from morning until noon, saying, “Baal, answer us!” But there was no sound;
 no one answered. Then they danced
 around the altar they had made.

43:
He walked in all the ways of his father Asa;
 he did not turn away from them but did what was right in the 
Lord
’s sight. However, the high places were not taken away;
 the people still sacrificed and burned incense on the high places.
